◆ ColorSpace

enum OVRPlugin.ColorSpace
Enumerator
Unknown 

The default value from GetHmdColorSpace until SetClientColorDesc is called. Only valid on PC, and will be remapped to Quest on Mobile.

Unmanaged 

No color correction, not recommended for production use. See documentation for more info.

Rec_2020 

Preferred color space for standardized color across all Oculus HMDs with D65 white point.

Rec_709 

Rec. 709 is used on Oculus Go and shares the same primary color coordinates as sRGB.

Rift_CV1 

Oculus Rift CV1 uses a unique color space, see documentation for more info.

Rift_S 

Oculus Rift S uses a unique color space, see documentation for more info.

Quest 

Oculus Quest's native color space is slightly different than Rift CV1.

P3 

Similar to DCI-P3. See documentation for more details on P3.

Adobe_RGB 

Similar to sRGB but with deeper greens using D65 white point.

◆ SpaceLocationFlags

enum OVRPlugin.SpaceLocationFlags : ulong

Space location flags.

See the OpenXR spc for more information.

Enumerator
OrientationValid 

Indicates that the pose field's orientation field contains valid data.

Applications must not read a pose field's orientation if this flag is unset.

PositionValid 

Indicates that the pose field's position field contains valid data.

Applications must not read a pose field's position if this flag is unset.

OrientationTracked 

Indicates that a pose field's orientation field represents an actively tracked orientation.

When a space location tracking an object whose orientation is no longer known during tracking loss (e.g. an observed QR code), the orientation will be a valid but untracked orientation and will be meaningful to use.

PositionTracked 

Indicates that a pose field's position field represents an actively tracked position.

When a space location loses tracking, the position will be a valid but untracked value that is inferred or last-known, e.g. based on neck model updates, inertial dead reckoning, or a last-known position, and will be meaningful to use.

Definition at line 1862 of file OVRPlugin.cs.

1863 {
1870 OrientationValid = 0x00000001,
1871
1878 PositionValid = 0x00000002,
1879
1888 OrientationTracked = 0x00000004,
1889
1898 PositionTracked = 0x00000008,
1899 }

◆ GetBodyState()

static bool OVRPlugin.GetBodyState ( Step  stepId,
ref BodyState  bodyState 
)
static

Gets the current BodyState associated with body tracking.

You can safely provide a zero-initialized BodyState as the bodyState parameter. However, if you call this method frequently (e.g., each frame), consider reusing an existing instance of BodyState to avoid per-frame allocations of the BodyState.JointLocations array.

Parameters
stepIdThe Step associated with the BodyState to get. Only see cref="Step.Render"/> is supported.
bodyStateOn success, bodyState will be populated with the BodyState associated stepId . You can safely pass a zero-initialized BodyState; BodyState.JointLocations will be reallocated if it is null or its length does not match the number of joint locations.
Returns
Returns true if the body state was successfully retrieved. Returns false otherwise.

99
100 if (_version > _versionZero && _version < OVRP_1_3_0.version)
101 throw new PlatformNotSupportedException(
102 "Oculus Utilities version " + wrapperVersion + " is too new for OVRPlugin version " +
103 _version.ToString() + ". Update to the latest version of Unity.");

107#endif
